  "generated_text": "To determine how many years it takes for Carlos to start earning money, we need to calculate the profit for each year.\n\n1.  **Analyze the costs and revenues:**\n    *   **Planting Cost:** $\\$90$ (This happens once at the beginning).\n    *   **Annual Water/Feed Cost:** $\\$3$ per year.\n    *   **Lemon Production:** The tree produces 7 lemons per year.\n    *   **Lemon Sales Price:** $\\$1.50$ per lemon.\n    *   **Earnings per Year:** $7 \\text{ lemons} \\times \\$1.50/\\text{lemon} = \\$10.50$.\n\n2.  **Calculate the annual profit:**\n    *   $\\text{Profit} = \\text{Revenue} - \\text{Costs}$\n    *   $\\text{Profit} = \\$10.50 - \\$3 = \\$7.50$ per year.\n\n3.  **Determine when profit becomes positive (or exceeds the initial investment):**\n    *   Carlos starts with a cost of $\\$90$.\n    *   He starts earning revenue in the first year (since he sells the lemons produced that year).\n    *   Let $n$ be the number of years.\n    *   Total Cost = $\\$90$.\n    *   Total Revenue after $n$ years = $n \\times \\$10.50$.\n    *   Total Cost of lemons after $n$ years = $n \\times \\$7.50$.\n    *   Profit after $n$ years = $(\\text{Total Revenue} - \\text{Total Cost of lemons}) - \\text{Planting Cost}$.\n   ",
